---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Digital Nomad Visa Greece | Taxomade">
  <main class="pt-32 pb-24 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 max-w-4xl mx-auto bg-white">
    <!-- Hero -->
    <div class="mb-16 border-b border-slate-100 pb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-black text-slate-900 mb-6 tracking-tight">Your Digital Nomad Visa for Greece <span class="text-blue-800">—</span> handled for you.</h1>
      <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-slate-600 mb-8 max-w-3xl">Live legally in Greece while working remotely. We prepare and manage your entire application.</p>
      <a href="/#configurator" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-4 text-lg font-bold rounded-lg text-white bg-slate-900 hover:bg-blue-800 transition-colors duration-200 shadow-sm">
        Check if you qualify
      </a>
    </div>

    <!-- What it is -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">What it is</h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
        The Greece Digital Nomad Visa lets non-EU citizens live in Greece for up to 12 months while working remotely for employers or clients <strong class="text-slate-900">outside</strong> Greece. It can be extended into a residence permit for up to two years total. It's designed for remote employees, freelancers and business owners whose income comes from abroad — you cannot work for a Greek employer on this visa.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Requirements -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">Requirements</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-4 text-lg text-slate-700 list-disc list-inside">
        <li>You must be a <strong class="text-slate-900">non-EU / non-EEA / non-Swiss</strong> citizen (EU citizens don't need a visa).</li>
        <li>Minimum <strong class="text-slate-900">€3,500 net per month</strong> income from outside Greece (+20% for a spouse, +15% per child — a couple with one child needs roughly €4,800/month).</li>
        <li>Proof of remote work: employment contract, client contracts, invoices, payslips or bank statements showing stable income.</li>
        <li>Valid passport, private health insurance, clean criminal record, proof of accommodation in Greece, and a declaration that you won't work for a Greek employer.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- How it works -->
    <section class="mb-16 bg-slate-50 p-8 md:p-10 rounded-2xl border border-slate-100">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-8">How it works</h2>
      
      <div class="mb-6 bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-800 p-4 rounded-r-lg">
        <p class="text-blue-900 font-medium"><em>Important 2026 change:</em> As of February 2026, you must apply at a <strong class="text-blue-900">Greek consulate in your home country before travelling</strong> — in-country applications are no longer possible.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-8 mt-10">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3 flex items-center"><span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-slate-900 text-white flex items-center justify-center mr-3 text-sm">1</span> What you do</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 ml-11">Gather your documents (we tell you exactly which), attend your consulate appointment, and travel to Greece once approved.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3 flex items-center"><span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-blue-800 text-white flex items-center justify-center mr-3 text-sm">2</span> What Taxomade does</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 ml-11">We review your situation, prepare and check your full document set, handle translations and legalizations, guide you through the consulate submission, and after arrival help you get your tax number (AFM) and residence permit. Processing typically takes around 1–3 months.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <p class="text-slate-500 mt-8 text-sm italic">Government fees (visa fee + €1,016 residence permit fee) are paid by you directly to the authorities and are separate from our service fee.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-8">FAQ</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="border-b border-slate-200 pb-6">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Can freelancers apply?</h4>
          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700">Yes — as long as you can document ongoing clients and income from outside Greece.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-b border-slate-200 pb-6">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Can I work for a Greek company?</h4>
          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700">No. Your income must come from abroad.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-b border-slate-200 pb-6">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Can my family come?</h4>
          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700">Yes, with higher income proof (+20% spouse, +15% per child). They can live but not work locally.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-b border-slate-200 pb-6">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Does it lead to tax residency?</h4>
          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700">If you stay more than 183 days, yes — and then you may qualify for the 50% tax break (see Article 5C).</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">How long is it valid?</h4>
          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700">12 months initially, extendable to two years.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Footer Disclaimer -->
    <div class="mt-20 pt-8 border-t border-slate-200 text-sm text-slate-500">
      <p>Taxomade is not a government body. We coordinate licensed local accountants and lawyers. Information is general and not individual legal or tax advice.</p>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
